From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Tue, 10 Feb 2026 21:18:58 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] PCI: cadence: sky1: skip regulator lookup under ACPI

Under ACPI, firmware manages PCIe endpoint power rails via power
resources (_PR0/_PR3).  The optional regulator lookup produces
spurious "dummy regulator" warnings since no DT regulator provider
exists.  Skip the devm_regulator_get_optional() call when booting
with ACPI.
---
 drivers/pci/controller/cadence/pci-sky1.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/cadence/pci-sky1.c b/drivers/pci/controller/cadence/pci-sky1.c
index 8b67daf8708d0..48930759f9873 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/cadence/pci-sky1.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/cadence/pci-sky1.c
@@ -1410,6 +1410,13 @@ static void sky1_pcie_parse_ep_pwr_supply(struct sky1_pcie *pcie)
 	pcie->str_pwron = device_property_read_bool(dev, "sky1,str-pwron");
 	pcie->std_pwron = device_property_read_bool(dev, "sky1,std-pwron");
 
+	/*
+	 * Under ACPI, firmware manages PCIe endpoint power rails via
+	 * power resources.  Skip the regulator lookup.
+	 */
+	if (ACPI_COMPANION(dev))
+		return;
+
 	/* optional power control for device */
 	pcie->vsupply = devm_regulator_get_optional(dev, "vcc-pcie");
 	if (IS_ERR(pcie->vsupply)) {
